    "recap_headline": "Rutgers University",
    "recap_text": "CHAMPAIGN, Ill. \u2013\nRutgers baseball dropped game one at Illinois by a score of 13-7 on Friday night at Illinois Field.\nThe Scarlet Knights (12-9, 2-2) were unable to complete the comeback against the Fighting Illini\u00a0(11-9, 3-4) after falling behind 9-1 in the first inning.\nAfter\nPeyton Bonds\nled off the game with a solo home run, Illinois responded with nine runs on nine hits in the bottom half to take control of the game.\nRU did its best to chip away, scoring two in the second on a two-run single from\nQuinten Perilli\n.\nCharlie Meglio\nadded a two-run homer in the third to make it 9-5 and\nTristan Salinas\nhomered in the fifth to make it a three-run game at 9-6.\nJordan Savi\u00f1on delivered a strong outing in relief, finishing the first inning and pitching 4.2 innings of relief, including four straight scoreless frames from the second through the fifth, adding eight strikeouts.\nIn the bottom of the sixth, the Illini added a pair on a two-run single to make it 11-6.\nThe teams traded late runs in the eighth on a Meglio sac fly and two-run sac fly for Illinois in the bottom half.\nOffensively,\nTrey Wells\ncontributed a four-hit day, while Meglio and Perilli each collected a pair of hits.\nRutgers will look to bounce back in game two of the series, set for 4 p.m. ET on Saturday afternoon.\nFollow Rutgers Baseball on Social Media\nX\n|\nInstagram\n|\nFacebook",
